title._content: Apollo 11 Mission Image - View of moon limb with Earth on the horizon, Mare Smythii Region

description._content: Collection: Johnson Space Center Media Archive Title: Apollo 11 Mission image - View of moon limb with Earth on the horizon, Mare Smythii Region Description: View of Moon limb with Earth on the horizon,Mare Smythii Region. Earth rise. This image was taken before separation of the LM and the Command Module during Apollo 11 Mission. Original film magazine was labeled V. Film Type: S0-368 Color taken with a 250mm lens. Foward overlap is 90%. Sun angle is High. Approximate Tilt is 75 degrees. Tilt direction is West (W). Source: www.archive.org/details/AS11-44-6562 Identifier: AS11-44-6562 SOURCE: nasaimages.org/luna/servlet/detail/NVA2~84~84~85902~137475 Visit www.nasaimages.org for the most comprehensive compilation of NASA stills, film and video, created in partnership with Internet Archive.
